---
title: Calendar Connect / Status / Disconnect Flow
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant TG as Telegram
    participant GW as bot-gateway
    participant CAL as calendar-service

    %% ── /calendar: нет подключения ──────────────────────────
    User->>TG: /calendar
    TG->>GW: message /calendar
    GW->>CAL: GET /connections?telegramUserId=X&scope=user
    CAL-->>GW: []
    GW->>CAL: POST /auth-url {provider: google, ...}
    CAL-->>GW: {url: "https://accounts.google.com/..."}
    GW->>TG: sendMessage("Calendar connection", [Connect Google Calendar])

    %% ── OAuth flow ───────────────────────────────────────────
    User->>TG: click "Connect Google Calendar"
    TG-->>User: opens browser → Google OAuth page
    User->>TG: approves access
    Note over User,TG: Google redirects to localhost:3000/calendar/google/callback?code=...&state=...
    GW->>CAL: POST /oauth-callback {code, state}
    CAL->>CAL: exchange code → tokens
    CAL->>CAL: encrypt & save CalendarConnection
    CAL-->>GW: connection saved

    %% ── /calendar: есть подключение ─────────────────────────
    User->>TG: /calendar
    TG->>GW: message /calendar
    GW->>CAL: GET /connections?telegramUserId=X&scope=user
    CAL-->>GW: [{provider: "google", ...}]
    GW->>TG: sendMessage("Google Calendar: connected", [Disconnect Google Calendar])

    %% ── отключение ───────────────────────────────────────────
    User->>TG: click "Disconnect Google Calendar"
    TG->>GW: callback calendar:disconnect:google
    GW->>CAL: DELETE /connections {provider: google, telegramUserId: X}
    CAL-->>GW: {ok: true}
    GW->>CAL: GET /connections?telegramUserId=X&scope=user
    CAL-->>GW: []
    GW->>TG: editMessage("Calendar connection", [Connect Google Calendar])
